	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think it's the RF modulator in the system that may need changed, not the switch.  I have a couple PAL clone systems that have RF out (of course 99% of the time I use the A/V instead), but I vaguely remember the picture being monchrome and having no sound.  The SNES one (Gamestation), kevtris helped me out by swapping an NTSC RF box into it when we had it taken apart, then it was fine.  Same RF box as the one from an NES.  I forget what it looks like inside the toploader though.
<br />
<br />Maybe you got lucky have a later revision.  The one I have has prominent bars that are really noticeable if you're on a full blank grey screen or something bright like that.
<br />
<br />The accessory included with the PAL FC clone I have was really neat though, it's an antenna that plugs into the RF out, and receiver for the TV's RF in.  I don't think the FCC would approve, heheh.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
