	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I think it's pretty clear the problem is inside the RF modulator in the console but I really don't understand : Why the same modulator would work fine in america and won't work in europe ? There is absolutely no reason or does it have to do with other waves interfering with it which aren't present in america ? Even that doesn't make any sense - I believe the modulator is the exact same and uses the same frequencies as the one in the PAL consoles, the only difference is that a NTSC video signal is modulated instead of a PAL video signal.</div>
<br />
<br />Unfortunately, not true: In NTSC, the audio signal is FM modulated at 4.5 MHz above baseband, and in PAL it's modulated at 5.5 MHz. I would have assumed your PAL TV that can take NTSC video in could also do the correct demodulation of audio, but maybe I'm wrong?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


